a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;</ph>.","pos":[72552,72867]},{"content":"You use <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/windows.services.maps.maplocationfinder.findlocationsasync.aspx\"&gt;</ph>FindLocationsAsync<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> for geocoding and <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/windows.services.maps.maplocationfinder.findlocationsatasync.aspx\"&gt;</ph>FindLocationsAtAsync<ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> for reverse geocoding.","pos":[72868,73244]},{"content":"Perform geocoding and reverse geocoding","pos":[73326,73365]},{"content":"Routes and directions.","pos":[73457,73479]},{"content":"Providing routes, distances, and directions between two geographical locations.","pos":[73497,73576]},{"content":"Google provides the web service <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>Google Maps Directions API<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> which can be used on Android although no SDK is provided.","pos":[73599,73732]},{"content":"Map Kit provides the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>MKDirections<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> API which can be used to fetch information about a route and directions.","pos":[73755,73878]},{"content":"You can request a walking or driving route with the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/windows.services.maps.maproutefinder.aspx\"&gt;</ph>MapRouteFinder<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> class in <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/windows.services.maps.aspx\"&gt;</ph>Windows.Services.Maps<ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;</ph>.","pos":[73901,74226]},{"content":"Routes are returned as a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/windows.services.maps.maproute.aspx\"&gt;</ph>MapRoute<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> instance which